[Since the last ProMED-mail post, there has only been one newly confirmed case, reported from Riyadh, while there have been 3 newly reported fatalities raising the reported case fatality rate to 40.7 percent. It is curious that the newly reported case was noted to be in stable condition, yet the same day as that report, the individual was reported as a fatality, suggesting there may have been a sudden fatal event (either cardiovascular, CNS (neurologic), or pulmonary in origin. It is also possible that the patient was noted to be in stable condition at the time of hospitalization, but by the time of report may have had a rapid decline.

A map showing the locations of the reported events can be found at the source URL. The HealthMap/ProMED map of Saudi Arabia can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5564064,131. - Mod.MPP]

